│ The function `planContainsAdditionalSimplifications` checks if the VPlan contains extra │
│ simplifications not accounted for in the legacy cost model. It does this by comparing   │
│ the instructions in the VPlan with those in the original loop. If there are             │
│ instructions in the loop that are not part of the VPlan or are skipped for cost         │
│ computation, it concludes that the VPlan contains additional simplifications.           │
│                                                                                         │
│ The assertion failure occurs because the function fails to validate the extra           │
│ simplifications in certain cases. To address this, we need to enhance the function to   │
│ handle discrepancies more robustly and provide better diagnostics.                      │
│                                                                                         │
│ ### Proposed Fix:                                                                       │
│ 1. **Enhance Logging**: Add detailed logging to `planContainsAdditionalSimplifications` │
│ to output the instructions that are mismatched between the VPlan and the original loop. │
│ This will help identify the root cause of the failure.                                  │
│ 2. **Improve Validation**: Modify the function to handle edge cases where instructions  │
│ are skipped or not part of the VPlan due to valid reasons (e.g., optimizations or       │
│ transformations).                                                                       │
│                                                                                         │
│ I will now proceed to implement the fix.                                                │
